## ✅ Pre-Production Testing Checklist

Run these before full deployment:

### Phase 1: Verify Components (5 min)
```bash
# 1. Boilerplate detection
docker compose exec web python -c "
from resources.utils.description_utils import is_boilerplate_description
assert is_boilerplate_description('CC BY ebook published by Springer') == True
assert is_boilerplate_description('A comprehensive introduction to biology') == False
print('✓ Boilerplate detection works')
"

# 2. Celery task
docker compose exec web python -c "
from resources.tasks import enrich_description_from_url
print('✓ Celery task imported successfully')
"

# 3. Signal handler
docker compose exec web python -c "
from resources.signals import enqueue_description_enrichment
print('✓ Signal handler imported successfully')
"

# 4. Model field
docker compose exec web python manage.py shell -c "
from resources.models import OERResource
field = OERResource._meta.get_field('description_last_enriched_at')
print(f'✓ Model field exists: {field.name}')
"

# 5. Migration applied
docker compose exec web python manage.py showmigrations resources | findstr "0016"

# Should show: [X] 0016_oerresource_description_last_enriched_at
```

### Phase 2: Test Signal Trigger (10 min)

```bash
# 1. Create test resource in shell
docker compose exec web python manage.py shell
```

```python
from resources.models import OERResource, OERSource

# Create test resource
source = OERSource.objects.first()
r = OERResource.objects.create(
    source=source,
    title="Test Book",
    url="https://example.com/test",
    description="CC BY ebook published by Springer"  # Boilerplate
)
print(f"Created resource {r.id}")
print(f"Before enrichment: {r.description_last_enriched_at}")
exit()
```

```bash
# 2. Watch Celery logs
docker compose logs -f celery | findstr /i "enriched enrichment"

# Should see task execution within ~30 seconds

# 3. Verify update
docker compose exec web python manage.py shell
```

```python
from resources.models import OERResource
r = OERResource.objects.get(id=<your_resource_id>)
print(f"After enrichment: {r.description_last_enriched_at}")
print(f"Populated: {'Yes' if r.description_last_enriched_at else 'No'}")
exit()
```

### Phase 3: Test Backfill Command (10 min)

```bash
# 1. Preview (safe, no changes)
docker compose exec web python manage.py backfill_descriptions_from_url --dry-run
# Should show candidates count and sample list

# 2. Find KBART source ID
docker compose exec web python manage.py shell
```

```python
from resources.models import OERSource
sources = OERSource.objects.filter(source_type__icontains='kbart')
for s in sources:
    print(f"ID: {s.id}, Name: {s.display_name}")
exit()
```

```bash
# 3. Test backfill with limit
docker compose exec web python manage.py backfill_descriptions_from_url \
  --source-id <KBART_ID> \
  --limit 5 \
  --dry-run
# Should show 5 candidates

# 4. Actual backfill (small batch)
docker compose exec web python manage.py backfill_descriptions_from_url \
  --source-id <KBART_ID> \
  --limit 5

# 5. Monitor execution
docker compose logs -f celery | findstr "Enriched description"
# Should see 5 success messages within 1-2 minutes
```

